    {
      "CVE": "CVE-2006-10003",
      "Description": "XML::Parser versions through 2.47 for Perl has an off-by-one heap buffer overflow in st_serial_stack.\n\nIn the case (stackptr == stacksize - 1), the stack will NOT be expanded. Then the new value will be written at location (++stackptr), which equals stacksize and therefore falls just outside the allocated buffer.\n\nThe bug can be observed when parsing an XML file with very deep element nesting",
      "Threats": [
        {
          "Type": "Impact",
          "Severity": "important"
        }
      ],
